OL,6,FBates initially blamed Mr Banks for
OL,7,Fthe collision, who was a recently-
OL,8,Fretired university lab assistant and
OL,9,Fpopular Scout leader.
OL,11,FHe claimed the pensioner's bike hit
OL,12,Fthe kerb then swerved in front of him,
OL,13,Fleaving him unable to avoid the bike.
OL,15,FHowever, Leicester Crown Court heard
OL,16,Fhow Bates' eight-year-old son, who was
OL,17,Ftaken to an ambulance after the crash,
OL,18,Fsaid his dad was at fault. He told a
OL,19,Fparamedic: "Daddy was trying to get a
OL,20,Fsong on that he liked. He didn't see a
OL,21,Fbike and we hit it."
