OL,6,FBates was charged with causing death
OL,7,Fby dangerous driving, which he denied,
OL,8,Finsisting that his phone was either in
OL,9,Fhis son's hands or in the car's
OL,10,Fcentral console when the crash
OL,11,Fhappened.
OL,13,FHe later changed his story and pleaded
OL,14,Fguilty to the lesser offence of
OL,15,Fcausing death by careless driving
OL,16,Fwhile over the drug-driving limit.
OL,18,FThe court heard Bates's blood
OL,19,Fcontained just over three times the
OL,20,Flegal limit for a by-product of
OL,21,Fcocaine use.
